WEBVTT

00:03.963 --> 00:07.091
Wow, Sheldon, I cannot believe
you made up your own game.

00:07.258 --> 00:10.970
Oh. Research Lab is more than a game.

00:11.137 --> 00:12.388
It's like the slogan says:

00:12.555 --> 00:16.642
"The physics is theoretical,
but the fun is real."

00:17.518 --> 00:19.812
We must not be playing it right.

00:21.230 --> 00:24.817
All right. Five.
One, two, three, four, five.

00:24.984 --> 00:26.235
Oh, wow, look at that.

00:26.402 --> 00:29.238
My Department of Defense
research grant is renewed.

00:29.405 --> 00:31.073
Oh. Great roll.

00:31.240 --> 00:33.993
Now you can demolish
your Soviet-style cyclotron...

00:34.160 --> 00:37.163
...and build the large hadron collider.

00:37.330 --> 00:39.206
YaY-

00:39.749 --> 00:41.334
You're a natural at this, Penny.

00:41.500 --> 00:44.128
And as the first beta testers,
you two have quite the edge...

00:44.295 --> 00:47.048
...when we play with Wolowitz
and Koothrappali on Sunday.

00:47.214 --> 00:51.177
Oh, gee, Sheldon,
I don't think we can play on Sunday.

00:51.344 --> 00:52.595
Why not?

00:52.762 --> 00:56.682
Because of the reasons
that Penny will now tell you. Penny?

00:56.849 --> 00:59.185
I have to pick up my friend Justin
from the airport.

00:59.352 --> 01:01.687
There you go.
She has to pick up her friend Justin.

01:01.854 --> 01:04.023
And I can't play
because I'm going with her. Right?

01:04.190 --> 01:06.525
Uh, yeah, if you want.
There may not be room.

01:06.692 --> 01:09.654
He's got a lot of stuff, like guitars
and amplifiers.

01:09.820 --> 01:12.573
Wait. What are you talking about?

01:12.740 --> 01:13.824
My friend Justin.

01:13.991 --> 01:16.786
Pay attention, Leonard.
That's why she can't play on Sunday.

01:16.994 --> 01:18.537
- Who is this Justin?
- Your turn.

01:18.704 --> 01:20.539
- I told you about him.
- Roll the dice.

01:20.706 --> 01:23.167
Yeah. My friend from Omaha,
plays the guitar.

01:23.334 --> 01:25.086
He's coming
looking for session work.

01:25.252 --> 01:27.380
So I told him
he could crash on my couch.

01:27.546 --> 01:31.717
Come on. Roll a six, Penny dies horribly
in a nuclear meltdown.

01:32.677 --> 01:35.388
See what I mean
when I say the fun is real?

01:36.222 --> 01:39.141
Hang on. Some guy
is gonna be sleeping on your couch?

01:39.308 --> 01:41.727
He's not some guy. He's my friend.

01:41.894 --> 01:45.022
So by friend, do you mean
"friend" friend...

01:45.189 --> 01:47.900
...gay friend, or "ex-boyfriend
you're now platonic with...

01:48.067 --> 01:50.486
...but still might have a thing for you"
friend?

01:50.945 --> 01:53.280
Well, he's definitely not gay.

01:53.447 --> 01:57.535
Oh. A definitely-not-gay musician
sleeping on my girlfriend's couch.

01:57.702 --> 01:59.453
Yippie.

01:59.620 --> 02:02.581
Okay, we went out a little bit
a long time ago.

02:02.748 --> 02:04.709
But we were never, like, going out.

02:04.875 --> 02:06.836
Okay. Not to be pedantic,
the last I checked...

02:07.002 --> 02:09.588
..."went out" was the past tense
of "going out"...

02:09.755 --> 02:11.924
...which I think we all know
is a popular euphemism...

02:12.091 --> 02:14.343
...for saw each other naked.

02:15.469 --> 02:17.471
I'll just roll for you.

02:18.264 --> 02:20.516
You have a problem
with Justin staying with me?

02:20.683 --> 02:22.101
What was your first clue?

02:22.268 --> 02:25.062
Uh-oh. Industrial accident.

02:25.646 --> 02:27.648
Know what?
Don't talk to me like an idiot.

02:27.815 --> 02:31.569
I'm not talking to you like an idiot.
I'm saying the whole idea is idiotic.

02:31.736 --> 02:36.615
"You accidentally stare at a helium-argon
laser. Lose one turn and a retina."

02:36.782 --> 02:38.784
How's that not talking to me
like I'm an idiot?

02:38.951 --> 02:41.662
It's my friend, it's my couch
and it's my freaking life.

02:41.829 --> 02:43.456
It's also your roll.

02:43.748 --> 02:45.499
You know what? It is your life.

02:45.666 --> 02:48.461
If you wanna have some stupid guitarist
stay on your couch, fine!

02:48.627 --> 02:51.756
Why don't you just rent bunk beds
and invite the Black Eyed Peas?

02:51.922 --> 02:56.343
Hey, if I wanna invite the line-up
of Lollapalooza to my apartment, I will.

02:56.510 --> 02:57.845
It's none of your business.

02:58.012 --> 03:00.431
Do you know how childish you sound
right now?

03:00.598 --> 03:04.810
- Oh, now I'm a child. Not an idiot anymore.
- Hey, the two aren't mutually exclusive.

03:04.977 --> 03:06.479
Oh, you are such a--

03:06.645 --> 03:07.730
[BLENDER WHIRRING]

03:07.897 --> 03:10.691
- What the hell is he doing?
- Drowning us out. He doesn't like fighting.

03:10.858 --> 03:13.402
Sheldon, just stop.
Look, the fight is over.

03:13.569 --> 03:16.697
Oh, and FYI. You never even heard
of the Black Eyed Peas...

03:16.864 --> 03:17.907
...until you met me.

03:18.073 --> 03:20.201
I heard of them.

03:20.868 --> 03:23.579
I didn't know they were a band.

03:24.789 --> 03:27.166
Sheldon, she's gone.
You can turn off the blender.

03:27.333 --> 03:29.084
[BLENDER STOPS]

03:33.422 --> 03:37.468
Has your relationship reached
its inevitable ugly end?

03:38.511 --> 03:41.263
No, we just had a little spat.

03:41.430 --> 03:44.517
Look on the bright side.
As a result of Penny's forfeit...

03:44.683 --> 03:49.063
...you have become
the world's first winner of Research Lab.

03:49.230 --> 03:52.024
Would you like a commemorative
snow cone?

04:19.969 --> 04:21.679
I don't get how she can just announce...

04:21.846 --> 04:24.139
...that an old boyfriend is gonna sleep
on her couch.

04:24.306 --> 04:26.725
Hey, I thought of a game
we can play in the car.

04:26.892 --> 04:28.292
I don't wanna play a game, Sheldon.

04:28.435 --> 04:31.564
It's called Scientists.
Now, I will name three scientists...

04:31.730 --> 04:35.609
...you'll put them in order of the size
of their contribution to their fields.

04:35.776 --> 04:37.528
To make this game
even more compelling...

04:37.695 --> 04:41.031
...you must consider only the
contribution of the man to the field...

04:41.198 --> 04:43.158
...not the validity of the field itself.

04:43.325 --> 04:45.536
For example,
Abu Musa Jabir ibn Hayyan...

04:45.703 --> 04:49.039
...made a greater contribution
to the discredited field of alchemy...

04:49.206 --> 04:51.584
...than Halbert Vanderplatt
made to neurobiology.

04:51.750 --> 04:53.669
Okay. Ready to have some fun?

04:54.920 --> 04:57.006
An old boyfriend
who's "definitely not gay."

04:57.172 --> 05:00.009
You know, that's what a guy
likes to hear. "Definitely."

05:00.175 --> 05:01.760
All right, I'll start with an easy one.

05:01.927 --> 05:05.723
Um, Isaac Newton, Madame Curie
and Niels Bohr.

05:05.890 --> 05:09.226
And then I say one little thing
and I end up being the bad guy.

05:09.393 --> 05:12.563
Hint. Madame Curie had her husband
to help her.

05:12.730 --> 05:14.023
What am I supposed to say?

05:14.189 --> 05:17.401
"Sure, Penny. I'm cool with your old
boyfriend sleeping in your apartment."

05:17.568 --> 05:20.195
[MOCKING PENNY]
"It doesn't matter if you're cool or not.

05:20.362 --> 05:23.490
Because I'm Penny, I'm pretty
and I can do whatever I want."

05:23.657 --> 05:27.328
[NORMAL VOICE] "You think you're doing a
favor by being in a relationship with me."

05:27.494 --> 05:30.706
[MOCKING PENNY] "No. I'm doing you
a favor by being in the same room as you."

05:30.873 --> 05:32.249
Leonard, stop the car.

05:33.709 --> 05:34.752
What?

05:34.919 --> 05:37.379
I can't listen to the two of you fight
anymore.

05:42.384 --> 05:45.137
- Come on. We're late.
- Calm down. We'll make the movie.

05:45.304 --> 05:49.099
I believe my alarm is appropriate.
The movie starts in 17 minutes.

05:49.266 --> 05:51.936
We'll need to make all the lights
on Colorado Boulevard.

05:52.102 --> 05:55.022
Plus, skip the concession stand
and pre-show urination.

05:55.940 --> 06:00.653
Oh, dude, I wish you had said something
before I pounded that last Red Bull.

06:00.819 --> 06:03.489
SHELDON:
Go. Go, Power Rangers, go.

06:05.783 --> 06:07.868
- Hey.
- Hey.

06:08.035 --> 06:10.913
- We're, uh, going to the movies.
- No, we're not.

06:12.164 --> 06:15.167
We're standing in the hallway,
suffering through an awkward encounter.

06:16.418 --> 06:17.795
Hang on.

06:18.337 --> 06:21.757
They're showing a digital <i>Time</i> Bandits.
You wouldn't wanna come, would you?

06:21.924 --> 06:23.384
Not really, no.

06:23.550 --> 06:26.261
All right. Invitation pointlessly offered,
declined as expected.

06:26.428 --> 06:29.598
Everyone's civil, nobody's fighting.
Have a nice evening.

06:31.767 --> 06:33.352
Just give us a minute?

06:33.519 --> 06:35.562
Take all the time you need.

06:39.400 --> 06:41.986
So are we gonna talk about last night?

06:42.152 --> 06:44.947
- Are you ready to apologize?
- No.

06:45.114 --> 06:47.950
Ehh! Wrong answer.
But thank you for playing.

06:48.117 --> 06:49.868
Come on. This is stupid.

06:50.035 --> 06:52.287
Oh, there it is again.
You think I'm stupid.

06:52.454 --> 06:55.165
No. There's a difference
between being and acting stupid.

06:55.332 --> 06:59.336
Oh, yeah? Well, there's a difference
between being a jerk and being an ass.

06:59.503 --> 07:02.798
No, there isn't. They're synonyms.

07:04.675 --> 07:06.885
Well, that was rather unpleasant.

07:07.219 --> 07:11.098
Yeah. I don't think I need
my pre-show urination anymore.

07:12.599 --> 07:14.643
Leonard, when that woman moved in
three years ago...

07:14.810 --> 07:18.731
...l told you not to talk to her.
Now look, we are late for the movies.

07:22.234 --> 07:25.362
<i>Hey, look Amazing Spider-Man 193.</i>

07:25.529 --> 07:26.864
Got it.

07:27.698 --> 07:29.992
Remember this one?
Spider-Man loses a big fight...

07:30.159 --> 07:32.494
...and then his girlfriend breaks up
with him.

07:35.664 --> 07:39.209
You want me to get it for you?
It will help take your mind off things.

07:39.710 --> 07:41.336
Hey, guys. What's going on?

07:41.503 --> 07:44.089
Ah, we need to kill a couple hours
until the next showing.

07:44.256 --> 07:45.799
Oh, well, no problem.

07:45.966 --> 07:48.135
I was thinking of closing early,
and going home...

07:48.302 --> 07:53.432
...but let's face it, that's just a smaller
lonely room filled with comic books.

07:54.641 --> 07:56.310
Thanks, Stuart.

07:57.352 --> 07:58.437
Let me ask you.

07:58.604 --> 08:01.857
Do you think it's okay to have
an ex-boyfriend sleep on her couch?

08:02.024 --> 08:03.984
- She's obviously way out of line.
- Thank you.

08:04.151 --> 08:07.237
But if she dumps you,
she'll have a new boyfriend by tomorrow...

08:07.404 --> 08:10.741
...and you'll have a new girlfriend
when you figure out how to build one.

08:12.826 --> 08:15.913
So the only question is,
how long until you fold?

08:16.080 --> 08:17.414
I am not gonna fold.

08:17.581 --> 08:21.710
Well, excuse me. I don't think
Penny's out of line. You don't own her.

08:21.877 --> 08:23.545
It's like my girl BeyoncÃ© says:

08:23.712 --> 08:26.507
"If you like it,
you should've put a ring on it."

08:27.841 --> 08:31.053
At the very least, when she found out
Leonard was upset about it...

08:31.220 --> 08:33.931
- ...she should've backed off.
- Like when a guy's upset...

08:34.098 --> 08:36.725
...his friend agreed to take a class
with him and then doesn't...

08:36.892 --> 08:39.728
...because he's doing a juice fast
with his mother?

08:40.187 --> 08:42.231
I didn't know you were upset
about that.

08:42.397 --> 08:46.443
Really? Did you miss the subtle indicators?
Like me saying, "Howard, I am upset."

08:46.610 --> 08:49.154
HOWARD: Okay, sorry.
- Maybe it's different in this country.

08:49.321 --> 08:52.199
Back in India, it means you're upset
with a guy named Howard.

08:52.366 --> 08:55.077
- I said I'm sorry.
- Sorry doesn't make up for the fact...

08:55.244 --> 08:57.704
...l had to make chicken and rice
with this vegan guy.

08:57.871 --> 09:01.750
Do you know
what vegan chicken and rice is? Rice.

09:01.917 --> 09:05.295
You think I was having fun? Sitting
around listening to my mother say:

09:05.462 --> 09:07.881
[AS MRS. WOLOWITZ] "Have you ever
peed so much in your life?"

09:08.048 --> 09:11.677
Oh, my God.
You are such a mama's boy.

09:11.844 --> 09:15.597
HOWARD: Don't bring my mother into this!
- You brought your mother into this!

09:15.764 --> 09:17.182
Stop it! Both of you!

09:17.349 --> 09:20.102
This fighting, I might as well be back
with my parents.

09:20.269 --> 09:23.021
[AS MOTHER] "I told you if you didn't
quit drinking, I'd leave you."

09:23.188 --> 09:26.942
[AS FATHER] "I guess that makes you a liar.
I'm drunk as hell and you're still here."

09:27.401 --> 09:29.570
[AS MOTHER] "Stop yelling.
You're making Sheldon cry."

09:29.736 --> 09:31.822
[AS FATHER]
"I'll tell you what's making Sheldon cry.

09:31.989 --> 09:33.448
That I let you name him Sheldon."

09:40.455 --> 09:43.375
Boy, what got him so upset?

09:43.542 --> 09:46.128
Oh, sure. You can tell
when Sheldon's upset.

09:53.635 --> 09:56.180
Oh. Thank you very much.
Come back soon.

09:57.014 --> 09:59.600
With the other half of my tip.

10:00.559 --> 10:01.685
[SIGHS]

10:01.852 --> 10:04.396
Hey, Sheldon.
What're you doing here?

10:04.563 --> 10:06.481
This is a restaurant. It's lunchtime.

10:06.648 --> 10:09.526
I'd think as a waitress you'd be familiar
with the paradigm.

10:09.985 --> 10:11.737
- Is Leonard coming'?
- No.

10:11.904 --> 10:15.449
I believe Leonard is waiting for you
to come back to him and apologize.

10:15.616 --> 10:17.993
- Well, that's not gonna happen.
- I assumed that.

10:18.160 --> 10:20.537
- Hence my true purpose in coming here.
- Which is?

10:20.704 --> 10:23.248
I want you to crawl back to him
and apologize.

10:23.415 --> 10:28.712
- I'm busy.
- Excuse me, miss. I'd like to order lunch.

10:32.341 --> 10:35.010
- Fine. What do you want?
- I have a few questions.

10:35.177 --> 10:38.055
First, I notice that you offer
soup and a half sandwich.

10:38.222 --> 10:39.473
- Yes.
- Where exactly...

10:39.640 --> 10:41.683
...does the half-sandwich come from?

10:41.850 --> 10:44.228
Are you giving me half
of someone else's sandwich?

10:44.770 --> 10:48.357
Or do I have to wait for someone else
to order the other half?

10:48.523 --> 10:50.609
No. Sheldon, they just make
a half sandwich.

10:50.776 --> 10:52.486
You can't make a half sandwich.

10:52.653 --> 10:56.156
If it's not half of a whole sandwich,
it's just a small sandwich.

10:56.323 --> 10:58.951
Okay, fine.
It's soup and a small sandwich.

10:59.117 --> 11:02.496
- Is that what you want?
- Of course not. I'll have my usual.

11:02.829 --> 11:04.665
- Great.
- Aren't you gonna ask...

11:04.831 --> 11:07.209
- ...if I want a beverage?
- Usually lemonade?

11:07.376 --> 11:08.418
- Yes.
- Want lemonade?

11:08.585 --> 11:09.711
- Yes.
- Anything else?

11:09.878 --> 11:11.546
Yes. I want you to apologize to Leonard.

11:12.798 --> 11:16.385
I am not going to apologize.
I've done nothing. He's overreacting.

11:16.551 --> 11:20.889
Irrelevant. The disruption in your
relationship is making my life intolerable.

11:21.056 --> 11:23.767
Well, I'm sorry, Sheldon,
but this really isn't about you.

11:24.601 --> 11:26.395
I don't follow.

11:27.312 --> 11:30.065
Yeah. Yeah, I'll be right there.
Look, Sheldon, I have to go.

11:30.232 --> 11:33.902
All right. Let's assume ad arguendum,
that in this case Leonard is wrong.

11:34.069 --> 11:36.655
- Leonard is wrong.
- Considering the transgressions...

11:36.822 --> 11:38.699
...you committed
that he's overlooked...

11:38.865 --> 11:41.368
...don't you think that
you could return the favor?

11:41.868 --> 11:43.537
I'm coming. Goodbye, Sheldon.

11:48.458 --> 11:51.253
What do you mean
transgressions I've committed?

11:51.420 --> 11:54.589
Were you under the impression that
Leonard has no complaints about you?

11:54.756 --> 11:56.466
Like what? Yeah, yeah, I see you.

11:56.633 --> 12:00.095
You're making a check sign in the air.
Got it. Just hold your horses.

12:00.554 --> 12:03.515
- What does Leonard complain about?
- Your driving.

12:03.682 --> 12:05.350
The stuffed animals on your bed...

12:05.517 --> 12:08.854
...that stare at him
during your amorous activities.

12:09.646 --> 12:11.815
Your constant tardiness, your singing.

12:11.982 --> 12:13.608
- My singing?
- That's from my list.

12:13.775 --> 12:16.194
Leonard'd be a fool
if he didn't agree with it.

12:16.361 --> 12:19.531
Okay, if Leonard has problems with me,
why hasn't he just said so?

12:19.698 --> 12:22.743
According to him, you're over-sensitive
and have a temper.

12:22.909 --> 12:27.289
Oh, really? Well, then do me a favor
and tell Leonard that he can drop dead.

12:31.335 --> 12:34.838
And she wonders
why she's constantly under-tipped.

12:38.717 --> 12:40.719
- Hey.
- Oh, good, you're home.

12:40.886 --> 12:42.596
- I need you to do me a favor.
- Sure.

12:42.763 --> 12:45.849
- Go apologize to Penny.
- What?

12:46.016 --> 12:47.059
Right now would be good.

12:47.225 --> 12:48.352
[BANGING ON DOOR]

12:48.518 --> 12:51.229
PENNY: Leonard!
- A few minutes ago would've been better.

12:51.813 --> 12:56.026
I hear you don't like my stuffed animals,
my driving or my punctuality.

12:56.193 --> 12:58.362
Who would tell you
something like that?

12:58.528 --> 13:00.822
Why would you tell her
something like that?

13:00.989 --> 13:03.367
It doesn't matter why he told me.
It's true, isn't it?

13:03.533 --> 13:06.119
Okay, yeah, it's true.
But I can live with that stuff.

13:06.286 --> 13:08.663
What I can't live with
is you casually informing me...

13:08.830 --> 13:11.708
...some guy is gonna be staying
without asking me first.

13:11.875 --> 13:14.503
That isn't even your problem.
Problem is you don't trust me.

13:14.669 --> 13:16.004
Oh, come on.

13:16.171 --> 13:19.383
Sheldon, have you ever once heard me say
that I don't trust Penny?

13:19.549 --> 13:21.468
Sheldon? Where did he go?

13:21.635 --> 13:24.179
Ugh. Your yelling must've
freaked him out again.

13:24.346 --> 13:27.224
Where are you going? You just walk away
in the middle of an argument?

13:27.391 --> 13:28.892
No. I'm gonna find your roommate...

13:29.059 --> 13:32.396
...before he hurts himself
trying to cross the street or something.

13:32.562 --> 13:33.605
Why didn't you say so?

13:33.772 --> 13:35.652
PENNY: Now I need your permission
for that too'?

13:35.816 --> 13:37.317
I can't read your mind, Penny.

13:37.484 --> 13:41.279
PENNY: Really? Why not?
You're so smart and I'm so dumb!

13:43.824 --> 13:46.827
Raj. Raj. Raj.

13:46.993 --> 13:49.579
RAJESH:
Stop knocking. It's open.

13:50.163 --> 13:52.624
Please tell my parents
that our dark matter research...

13:52.791 --> 13:56.545
...is at a critical juncture. I can't come
for my cousin Sanjay's wedding.

13:56.711 --> 13:59.840
<i>Ask our son what we're supposed
to say to Mr. and Mrs. Chaudri...</i>

14:00.006 --> 14:03.760
<i>...whose daughter, Lakshmi, is flying in
for the sole purpose of meeting him.</i>

14:03.927 --> 14:05.595
I didn't ask you to set me up.

14:05.762 --> 14:09.766
<i>- You should be thanking us.
- Yes, Lakshmi got her stomach stapled.</i>

14:10.684 --> 14:12.936
<i>You have an opportunity
to get in with her...</i>

14:13.103 --> 14:15.730
<i>...before she loses weight
and her self-esteem goes up.</i>

14:15.897 --> 14:17.190
I don't care.

14:17.357 --> 14:19.776
And why don't you think
I can find a woman for myself?

14:19.943 --> 14:21.778
<i>You're 27, the closest thing
we have...</i>

14:21.945 --> 14:24.781
<i>to a daughter-in-law
is that Jewish boy, Howard.</i>

14:24.948 --> 14:27.701
Oh, that is completely below the belt.

14:27.868 --> 14:31.329
Sheldon, tell my parents
that Howard and I are just friends.

14:31.830 --> 14:33.081
Sheldon?

14:33.248 --> 14:35.584
Howard and I are just friends.

14:39.129 --> 14:41.882
Fine. I'll come home
for Sanjay's wedding.

14:45.677 --> 14:47.179
Sheldon.

14:47.345 --> 14:48.472
[WHISTLES]

14:50.182 --> 14:52.809
What are you doing?
He's not a lost dog.

14:52.976 --> 14:54.811
Hey, why don't you just let me find him...

14:54.978 --> 14:57.606
...while you sit there
hitting your imaginary brake?

14:57.772 --> 15:01.485
The brake might be imaginary,
but that stop sign you just ran wasn't.

15:01.651 --> 15:05.739
- What stop sign?
- Eyes on the road. Eyes on the road!

15:13.038 --> 15:14.539
[DOORBELL RINGS]

15:14.706 --> 15:18.585
MRS. WOLOWITZ:
Howard, answer the door! I'm busy!

15:18.752 --> 15:21.171
HOWARD:
I'm busy too! You answer it!

15:21.338 --> 15:23.965
MRS. WOLOWITZ:
I can't! I'm on the toilet!

15:24.883 --> 15:26.801
HOWARD:
God's sake, I don't need to hear that!

15:26.968 --> 15:29.012
Can't you just say, "I'm busy?"

15:29.179 --> 15:32.849
MRS. WOLOWITZ: I said, "I'm busy,"
but that wasn't good enough for you!

15:33.016 --> 15:35.393
HOWARD: I hope it's one
of those home invasion deals...

15:35.560 --> 15:37.354
...and they shoot me in the head.

15:37.521 --> 15:42.734
MRS. WOLOWITZ: Well, if it's a home
invader, don't tell them I'm on the toilet!

15:46.154 --> 15:47.989
There's no one there.

15:48.156 --> 15:51.201
You're hearing things,
you crazy old lady.

15:54.496 --> 15:56.248
Hey, Stuart. Have you seen Sheldon?

15:56.414 --> 15:59.334
Yeah. He's, uh, over in the
graphic novel section.

16:01.211 --> 16:03.129
Built himself a little nest.

16:03.588 --> 16:05.340
Thank you.

16:05.674 --> 16:07.050
- Uh, Penny.
- Yeah?

16:07.217 --> 16:09.511
- Is everything okay?
- What do you mean?

16:09.678 --> 16:12.138
Uh, Sheldon told me you and Leonard
are having a fight.

16:12.305 --> 16:15.183
Oh, yeah, kind of. It's no big thing.

16:15.350 --> 16:16.643
STUART:
Oh, good. Good.

16:17.477 --> 16:19.479
I love you.

16:20.605 --> 16:22.983
I'm not leaving until you talk to me.

16:23.149 --> 16:25.443
- Hey, what's going on?
- It's a little hard to explain.

16:25.610 --> 16:28.154
He pretends
he's in an alternate dimension...

16:28.321 --> 16:33.368
...that occupies the same physical space
we're in, but he can't perceive us.

16:34.244 --> 16:37.455
Don't flatter yourself.
I'm just ignoring you.

16:38.957 --> 16:42.085
All right, come on, Sheldon,
let's go home. We're done fighting.

16:42.252 --> 16:43.587
I've heard that before.

16:43.753 --> 16:46.089
Then the next thing you know,
I'm hiding in my bedroom...

16:46.256 --> 16:50.051
...blaring a Richard Feynman lecture,
Morn shouting Jesus would forgive her...

16:50.218 --> 16:52.887
...if she put ground glass
in my dad's meat loaf.

16:53.930 --> 16:58.268
And my dad's on the roof skeet shooting
her Franklin Mint collectible plates.

16:59.477 --> 17:02.897
Okay, there's gonna be no more shouting
and no skeet shooting.

17:03.064 --> 17:05.942
Really? Where's your friend Justin
going to sleep?

17:06.568 --> 17:10.572
- Yeah, where is he gonna sleep?
- Oh, my God, would you let this go?

17:10.739 --> 17:12.782
I'd let it go.

17:13.825 --> 17:17.621
Why should I let it go? Why don't you
just tell the guy to find a place to sleep?

17:17.787 --> 17:19.372
[TOY BLARING MUSIC]

17:19.539 --> 17:21.333
Oh, for God sakes.

17:21.499 --> 17:23.001
[MUSIC STOPS]

17:23.168 --> 17:25.003
So you have childhood issues.

17:25.170 --> 17:26.921
We all have childhood issues.

17:27.088 --> 17:29.924
At some point, you just need to grow up
and get past them.

17:30.091 --> 17:31.217
<i>TOY".
Fire. Fire.</i>

17:31.384 --> 17:32.510
[LASER SOUND EFFECTS FIRING]

17:32.677 --> 17:34.262
Leonard, let me handle this. Please?

17:34.429 --> 17:37.307
- Fire, fire.
- Look, let-- She--

17:37.474 --> 17:39.392
[TOY CONTINUES INDISTINCTLY]

17:40.393 --> 17:41.728
[TOY STOPS]

17:42.979 --> 17:45.440
Sheldon, please try and understand.

17:45.607 --> 17:49.778
Look, Leonard and I are in a relationship
and occasionally we're gonna fight.

17:49.944 --> 17:54.032
But no matter what happens
between us, we will always love you.

17:56.034 --> 17:57.452
Right, Leonard?

17:57.952 --> 17:59.954
Always is a long time.

18:01.998 --> 18:03.958
Sure. Always.

18:04.125 --> 18:08.421
You know, how about we buy you
this robot and then we all go home?

18:09.089 --> 18:11.091
I want that one.

18:11.591 --> 18:13.218
Okay, you can have that one.

18:13.385 --> 18:15.887
Oh, come on.
He's just gonna play with it twice...

18:16.054 --> 18:19.432
...and then it'll end up in his closet
with all the other junk.

18:20.225 --> 18:21.643
Buy him the robot, Leonard.

18:23.812 --> 18:26.898
- Can I get this comic book too?
- Yes, you can.

18:31.444 --> 18:32.946
[PENNY SIGHS]

18:33.113 --> 18:34.239
We meet again.

18:42.997 --> 18:46.334
So, what did Justin say when you told him
he couldn't sleep on your couch?

18:46.501 --> 18:50.630
He's a musician.
He'll sleep in his own vomit if he has to.

18:59.222 --> 19:04.227
I should have asked for much more
than a comic book and a robot.

19:31.546 --> 19:33.548
[ENGLISH - US - SDH]
